      <p>
        For each of the following situations, what kind of function
        might you choose to encode the dependence? Give reasons for
        your answer. (6) 
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li>
          The hours of sunlight per day as a function of time
          measured in years. 
        </li>
        <li>
          The rate of tree growth as a function of hours of sunlight.
        </li>
        <li>
          The average temperature as a function of lattitude. 
        </li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        For each of the following functions, express the function as
        the composition of two other functions. (6) 
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li>
          <m>\sqrt{3x^2 + x^4}</m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>\frac{1}{\ln (x^2 + 1)}</m>
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>\tan (x^2 + 1) + \cot (x^2 + 1)</m>
        </li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        For the following pairs of functions <m>f</m> and <m>g</m>,
        calculate <m>f \circ g</m> and <m>g \circ f</m>. Simplify the
        expressions for the composition as much as you can. Then state
        the domains of <m>f</m>, <m>g</m>. <m>f \circ  g</m> and <m>g
        \circ f</m>. (18) 
      </p>
      <p><ol>
        <li>
          <m>f(x) = \frac{1}{x+1}</m> and <m>g(x) = x^2 + 7 </m>. 
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>f(x) = e^x</m> and <m>g(x) = x^3 + 3x^2 + 4x = 9</m>. 
        </li>
        <li>
          <m>f(x) = \sin \left( \frac{x}{4} \right)</m> and <m>g(x) =
          \sqrt{x+2}</m>. 
        </li>
      </ol></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
